title: As malnutrition deaths are reported and hunger grows, will 'famine' be declared in Gaza?
description: After months of aid agencies' warnings that Palestinians in Gaza Strip were at a high risk of famine, many worry it is now taking hold in the northern part of the enclave where children have begun to die of malnutrition and dehydration.

title: Doctors found tiny microplastics in people’s arteries. Their presence was tied to a higher risk of heart disease.
description: People with microplastics and nanoplastics in plaque lining a major blood vessel in their neck may have a higher risk of heart attack, stroke or death, new research suggests.

title: At least 2 killed on shipping vessel in first fatal Houthi attack since start of Israel-Hamas war
description: At least two sailors were killed Wednesday in a Houthi attack on a Barbados-flagged shipping vessel in the Gulf of Aden, American and British officials said, marking the first fatal attack by the group since the start of the Israel-Hamas war.

title: Gaza cease-fire talks continue amid push to get a deal done by Ramadan
description: Hamas said it’s pushing forward with cease-fire talks in Cairo despite Israel not sending a delegation for the negotiations. NBC News’ Molly Hunter reports on the urgency to get a cease-fire deal done before the start of Ramadan.

title: Navalny's widow calls on supporters to join an election day protest against Putin
description: Yulia Navalnaya, widow of opposition leader Alexei Navalny, called on Russians to join a March 17 election day protest to vote against President Vladimir Putin or spoil their ballots.

title: Elderly Gaza City resident dies from malnutrition, dehydration after dayslong siege, son says
description: Abdul Rahman Al-Dahdouh's son told an NBC News crew that they had been under siege for nine days in a Gaza City neighborhood, leading to the old man's death from dehydration and malnutrition.
